Ruth Franklin's Artistic Touch https://www.ruthfranklinbonnaz.com/posts/specialmachines/ -<p>The Cording, Braid &amp; Special Machines Book is 122 pages long and covers the unique functionalities of the specialty Cornely machines. Ruth overviews the first-hand knowledge that she acquired from two French gentlemen who claimed to have been taught by Antoine Bonnaz himself.</p>
<p>This book gives an overview of the functionalities of the <em>five</em> Cornely machines types categorized as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Group 1:</strong>  Basic Universal Feed Machines. <em>&ldquo;A&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;AB&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;A2&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;AH2&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;B&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;C&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;E&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;LE&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;LEG&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;LEGB&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;BCH&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;ACH&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;LCH&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;LGCH&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;RE&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;K&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;KB&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;L&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;LB&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;LG&rdquo;,</em> <em>&ldquo;LGB&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;LT&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;LTG&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;N&rdquo;</em>, and <em>&ldquo;X.&rdquo;</em></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Group 2:</strong>  Universal Feed Machines with oscillating hook &amp; bobbin. <em>&ldquo;F&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;FD&rdquo;</em>, <em>&ldquo;FA&rdquo;</em>, and <em>&ldquo;FBN.&rdquo;</em></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Group 3:</strong>  Numbered Cornely Machines that lock stitch, hemstitch, and satin stitch.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Group 4:</strong>  Specialty Cornely Machines and as Ruth puts it <em>&ldquo;they do very unusual things.&rdquo;</em></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Group 5:</strong>  Post-WWII redesign of Cornely Machines for the modern era. <em>Type 121</em> and <em>Type 148</em></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p>The end of the Special Machines book gives a sample of the contents of <a href="https://www.ruthfranklinbonnaz.com/posts/lettering">The Lettering Book</a> as well.</p>
